[2026-03-06]
- User report: UI crashes when adding `inline_button` module.
- Root cause identified in `src/etrax/standalone/config_vue.js`:
  - render-bound methods were mutating reactive state:
    - `currentStepButtons(editor)` assigned `step.buttons` on each render.
    - `inlineButtonDraft(editor)` assigned `_inline_button_draft` on each render.
  - This can trigger recursive Vue updates and crash the UI when inline_button editor is shown.
- Fix applied:
  - made render-read methods side-effect free:
    - `currentStepButtons(editor)` now only returns normalized buttons.
    - `inlineButtonDraft(editor)` now only returns normalized draft snapshot.
  - added explicit mutation helpers for event handlers:
    - `ensureStepButtons(editor)`
    - `normalizeInlineButtonDraft(rawDraft)`
    - `ensureInlineButtonDraft(editor)`
  - updated button action methods to mutate only through ensure helpers:
    - `saveInlineButton`, `cancelInlineButtonEdit`, `editInlineButton`,
      `moveInlineButtonUp`, `moveInlineButtonDown`, `removeInlineButton`,
      `updateInlineButtonDraftField`.
