[2026-04-02 11:25:01 +07:00] Updated share_location to stop silently auto-skipping when location data already exists. Added explicit run_if_context_keys and skip_if_context_keys support through the Vue editor, token UI serialization, standalone runtime config resolution, and Telegram share_location execution/tests so location prompts now follow configured conditions instead of implicit existing-location checks.
[2026-04-06 09:08:42 +07:00] Added live breadcrumb tracking support to share_location. Extended share_location config/runtime with track_breadcrumb for live-location requests, kept tracked requests active after the first accepted live point, appended later edited live-location updates into breadcrumb context/profile summary fields, enabled edited_message polling/profile logging for those updates, exposed the Track As Breadcrumb option in the share_location Vue editor/JSON serialization, and cleared the new breadcrumb fields in forget_user_data.
[2026-04-06 09:14:27 +07:00] Polished standalone config-ui checkbox styling. Updated the shared .checkbox CSS in token_ui to use a bordered pill-style control with stronger spacing/hover states, and switched the share_location, send_photo, and cart_button Vue editor checkboxes to the shared checkbox markup so those module toggles render consistently instead of using raw browser defaults.
[2026-04-06 09:19:52 +07:00] Fixed share_location primary-step checkbox persistence in the standalone config UI. Added hidden form fields for require_live_location and track_breadcrumb in config_vue, threaded those values through token_ui form parsing/builders/extractors for start/command/callback primary modules, and added token_ui regression coverage so the live-location checkboxes now round-trip on save/load instead of being dropped by form submission.
[2026-04-06 10:40:47 +07:00] Fixed remaining share_location checkbox reload persistence in the standalone config UI. Preserved require_live_location and track_breadcrumb in the command/callback row payloads returned to the Vue editor after save/load, added default empty values for new rows, and added regression tests covering command-row and callback-row rehydration so the Allow Only Live Location and Track As Breadcrumb toggles now stay checked after reload.
[2026-04-06 10:43:20 +07:00] Fixed the remaining share_location Track As Breadcrumb checkbox persistence bug in the Vue editor. Updated the shared module-system step normalizer to preserve track_breadcrumb during config-state rehydration while still requiring require_live_location, and verified the fix with node syntax check plus a direct parsePrimary smoke run for share_location.
[2026-04-06 11:01:26 +07:00] Added breadcrumb sampling controls to share_location. Extended the standalone editor and token_ui save/load path with breadcrumb_interval_minutes and breadcrumb_min_distance_meters for live-location breadcrumb tracking, preserved the new fields through Vue normalization and chain-step serialization, and updated the Telegram runtime so tracked live-location points are stored when either the configured time interval or minimum movement distance is reached. Verified with py -3 -m compileall src tests, node --check for config_vue.js, module_system.js, and share_location_module.js, plus focused inline-Python smoke coverage of the updated share-location runtime and token-ui cases because pytest is not installed.
[2026-04-06 11:21:10 +07:00] Added daily location-history storage for share_location. Introduced a store_history_by_day share_location option in the standalone editor and token_ui save/load path, preserved it through Vue normalization and chain-step serialization, and updated the Telegram runtime to append accepted location shares into location_history_by_day and accepted breadcrumb points into location_breadcrumb_by_day using per-day YYYY-MM-DD buckets. Also cleared the new daily history keys in forget_user_data and added focused runtime, token-ui, share-location, and forget-user-data regression coverage. Verified with py -3 -m compileall src tests, node --check for config_vue.js, module_system.js, and share_location_module.js, plus focused inline-Python smoke coverage because pytest is not installed.
[2026-04-06 11:42:26 +07:00] Added reusable command_module support so callback routes can load existing command pipelines for submenu-style flows. Wired command_module through standalone runtime execution, config persistence, Vue module editor, and focused regression coverage for command-module runtime/config/token-ui paths.
[2026-04-06 12:11:44] Added callback-local temporary command submenu support: callbacks can now save nested temporary commands in config, activate chat-scoped Telegram command menus via setMyCommands scope=chat, dispatch those temporary commands before global commands, and restore the main menu after the temporary command finishes. Updated runtime router/manager, callback config save-load/UI, nested module validation, and focused smoke coverage.
[2026-04-06 13:38:29] Fixed callback submenu save regression: removed stray temporary_commands_text reference from _build_command_modules_from_form so normal command config saves no longer raise NameError during token_ui config POST.
2026-04-06
- Fixed temporary callback submenu activation when a normal command loads a callback pipeline via `callback_module`. `handle_message_update()` now passes command-menu state and gateway context into `execute_pipeline()`, so `/etrex -> callback_module("tracking location")` can activate the callback's temporary command menu the same way as a direct callback click.
- Added a regression test covering `/etrex` loading `tracking location`, activating the temporary submenu, and restoring the main command menu after `/next`.
- Added a config-editor example scaffold for temporary callback menus. The new `Add eTrax Temp Menu Example` action creates `/etrax` plus callback `etrax` with example temporary commands for `/next`, `/route`, `/distance`, `/clear`, `/genstations`, and `/optimize`, so users can start from the original submenu plan without building every row manually.
- Renamed the scaffold action to `Add module with temp command` and simplified the generated example. It now creates `/temp_menu` plus callback `temp_menu` with only two sample temporary commands: `/command1` and `/command2`.
- Added a per-temporary-command checkbox in the config UI to control whether that temp command restores the original command menu after it runs. Old configs default to restore-on-run, and runtime restore now follows the per-command flag instead of always resetting after every temporary command.
- Updated the config-editor scaffold button label from `Add module with temp command` to `Add command with temp command` to match the command-focused workflow terminology in the editor.
- Simplified callback temp-command UI so callbacks without temporary commands no longer show the full submenu section. The editor now shows only an `Add Temporary Command` action until at least one temp command exists, then expands the full temporary command block.
- Added a `Clear Temporary Commands` action inside the callback temp-command section so a callback row can drop all temporary submenu commands at once without removing them one by one.
- Tightened callback temp-command UI state so the full temporary-command section only auto-opens from saved temp commands. Blank draft rows no longer count as persisted temp commands, and callback list keys now use stable callback identifiers to reduce stale Vue row state.
- Fixed the callback temp-command action label to use the same visibility rule as the section itself. `Add Another Temporary Command` now appears only when the temp-command section is actually open for that callback, instead of being driven by raw draft-row count alone.
- Fixed callback temp-command add behavior so clicking `Add Temporary Command` on a callback with no real temp commands reuses a hidden blank draft instead of creating a second blank temporary command row.
[2026-04-07 10:37:00 +07:00] Added a reserved built-in `/restart` command for standalone runtime command routing. `/restart` now always resolves to forget_user_data so it resets the current user back to the bot's original state, is published in the normal command menu by default when command menus are enabled, is auto-injected into every callback temporary command menu, and explicitly clears any active temporary menu override after it runs. Updated resolver and runtime_update_router coverage for built-in restart command resolution, temporary menu publishing, and restart-based submenu exit. Verified with py -3 -m py_compile on the touched runtime files and tests plus focused direct smoke execution because full pytest is not installed in this environment.
[2026-04-07 10:42:00 +07:00] Corrected the built-in `/restart` behavior so it no longer clears saved user data. The reserved restart command now reuses the configured `/start` flow as a safe reset back to the main bot state while still clearing any active temporary command menu override after it runs. Updated focused resolver coverage to verify `/restart` mirrors the start pipeline instead of forget_user_data and re-verified the temporary-menu restart exit path with direct smoke execution because full pytest is not installed in this environment.
[2026-04-07 10:56:30 +07:00] Reintroduced breadcrumb session guidance for share_location live tracking. Added editable breadcrumb started/interrupted/ended text templates to share_location config, standalone Vue editor, token_ui save-load/rehydration, and chain-step serialization; added a built-in End Breadcrumb inline callback that closes the active breadcrumb flow, archives finished breadcrumb sessions into location_breadcrumb_sessions, and keeps interrupted live-location breadcrumbs resumable until the user explicitly ends them. Updated runtime callback dispatch to pass gateway/bot_token/location store into built-in callback handlers, cleared archived sessions in forget_user_data, and added focused regression coverage plus direct smoke execution for breadcrumb start, interruption, end-session archive, and config round-trip behavior. Verified with py -3 -m compileall src tests, node --check for config_vue.js/module_system.js/share_location_module.js, and inline smoke tests because pytest is not installed.
[2026-04-07 11:09:00 +07:00] Recreated the standalone route module using breadcrumb data. Added core route config/module helpers that summarize active breadcrumb points and fall back to the latest archived breadcrumb session, generate Google Maps route links, compute segment and total distance, and expose route_* context fields. Wired the new route module through the runtime registry, token_ui config save-load path, Vue module editor, and JSON chain-step serialization with route_empty_text and route_max_link_points support. Verified with py -3 -m compileall src tests, node --check for route_module.js/config_vue.js/module_system.js, direct route/token-ui smoke tests, and a runtime registry smoke execution because pytest is not installed.
[2026-04-07 11:18:00 +07:00] Fixed standalone config-editor focus loss while typing temporary command rows. Switched callback and temporary-command Vue list keys to stable internal entry ids instead of mutable command text/index combinations, and added callback entry ids during state normalization so inputs no longer remount on each keystroke. Verified with node --check src\etrax\standalone\config_vue.js.
[2026-04-07 11:34:00 +07:00] Fixed /restart temporary-menu restoration so the visible command menu returns immediately. Threaded the resolved main command list through the runtime snapshot/update router and updated the temp-menu restore helper to delete the chat-scoped temporary menu then republish the main command list globally, instead of relying only on Telegram fallback behavior. Added focused restart-menu regression coverage and verified with py_compile plus a direct smoke execution of the restart temp-menu test.
[2026-04-07 11:42:00 +07:00] Made callback temporary command menus survive bot restarts. Added a file-backed temporary command menu state store that persists the active source callback key per bot/chat, wired runtime update routing to save active temp-menu state on callback activation and clear it on restore, and added lazy recovery so incoming commands rebuild the active temp menu from current config when in-memory state was lost after a process restart. Added focused JSON-store and runtime-router regression coverage and verified with py_compile plus direct smoke execution because full pytest is not installed.
[2026-04-07 11:45:00 +07:00] Fixed temporary callback-menu activation after adding persisted temp-menu state. Threaded temporary_command_menu_state_store through execute_pipeline recursion and the callback_module / command_module / inline_button_module helper paths so loaded callback pipelines can activate temporary command menus without raising a missing keyword-only argument error. Verified with py_compile and a direct smoke execution of the callback-module temp-menu activation test.
[2026-04-07 13:31:00 +07:00] Restored visible temporary command menus on bot startup. Added list_active_menus support to the temporary command menu state store and updated BotRuntimeManager to rebuild persisted active callback temp menus into memory and republish their chat-scoped Telegram command lists immediately after runtime snapshot load, so users no longer need to rerun the parent command after a bot restart just to see or use temp commands again. Verified with py_compile and direct inline smoke execution because pytest is not installed.
[2026-04-07 13:47:00 +07:00] Investigated repeated Telegram HTTP 409 polling conflicts for Testing 2. Confirmed there are no duplicate saved bot tokens in data/tokens.json, then added a local per-token polling lock in BotRuntimeManager so separate eTrax runtime processes on the same machine can no longer poll the same Telegram token simultaneously. The lock now uses an atomic token-fingerprint lock file with PID-based stale-lock cleanup, replacing the previous in-process-only protection. Added a focused cross-process lock test and verified with py_compile, compileall, a direct duplicate-token check, and an inline two-process lock smoke run because pytest is not installed.
[2026-04-07 14:05:00 +07:00] Added configurable breadcrumb resume messaging for share_location live tracking. Introduced breadcrumb_resumed_text_template through ShareLocationConfig/PendingLocationRequest, standalone runtime config resolution, Vue editor defaults/serialization, config_vue hidden form fields, and token_ui save-load/rehydration so the field round-trips cleanly for start, command, callback, and chain-step share_location configs. Updated the runtime breadcrumb flow to send a one-time resumed guidance message with the End Breadcrumb inline button when a live breadcrumb resumes after an interruption, and extended focused regression coverage for runtime interruption/resume plus token_ui breadcrumb field persistence. Also fixed an import-level regression by re-exporting DEFAULT_BREADCRUMB_RESUMED from etrax.core.telegram.__init__.py. Verified with py_compile, node --check, compileall, and import smoke checks because pytest is not installed in this environment.
[2026-04-07 14:18:00 +07:00] Fixed a Windows-specific polling lock crash in BotRuntimeManager. The local duplicate-poller guard was using os.kill(pid, 0) to probe stale lock-file PIDs, and on Windows stale PIDs can raise WinError 87 ('The parameter is incorrect') instead of ProcessLookupError. _process_exists now treats WinError 87 as a stale/non-running PID so the runtime cleans up the old polling lock instead of surfacing a runtime error. Added focused coverage in tests/test_polling_token_lock.py and verified with py_compile, compileall, and an inline smoke check because pytest is not installed in this environment.
[2026-04-08 09:15:00 +07:00] Investigated inline-button label edits not sticking in the standalone config editor. Updated config_vue.js so inline-button editor fields and button rows read from stable per-step reactive state instead of freshly normalized copies on each render; this keeps button text edits bound to the same draft/button objects through the Edit -> Update cycle and avoids losing inline button name changes in the UI. Planned verification: node --check src\etrax\standalone\config_vue.js.
[2026-04-08 09:32:00 +07:00] Investigated intermittent duplicate action execution in standalone runtime. Added callback-query idempotency in runtime_update_router so repeated delivery of the same Telegram callback_query.id is acknowledged again but only executed once within a short TTL window, and threaded the per-bot processed-callback cache through BotRuntimeManager. Added focused regression coverage in tests/test_bot_runtime_manager.py for replaying the same callback id twice. Planned verification: py -3 -m py_compile src\etrax\standalone\runtime_update_router.py src\etrax\standalone\bot_runtime_manager.py tests\test_bot_runtime_manager.py.
[2026-04-08 09:41:00 +07:00] Investigated `[WinError 11] An attempt was made to load a program with an incorrect format` on standalone runtime startup for `Testing 2`. Traced the failure to eager import of `cryptography` from paymentPayway.py via the PayWay payment module import chain, which was loading even for bots that do not use payway_payment. Moved the cryptography import inside paymentPayway.encrypt_source() and converted import/load failures into a targeted runtime error only when PayWay is actually executed. Planned verification: py -3 -m py_compile paymentPayway.py src\etrax\core\telegram\payway_payment.py src\etrax\standalone\runtime_module_registry.py.
[2026-04-08 10:14:00 +07:00] Continued investigating the recurring `Testing 2` `[WinError 11]` runtime failure after the PayWay import fix. Confirmed the standalone runtime was still collapsing exceptions to a single-line `str(exc)` message, then updated runtime error reporting so BotRuntimeManager logs the exception class plus full traceback through runtime_support TRACE lines while keeping the UI/runtime status message concise. Added focused coverage for multiline runtime error printing. Planned verification: py -3 -m pytest -q tests\test_runtime_support.py and py -3 -m py_compile src\etrax\standalone\bot_runtime_manager.py src\etrax\standalone\runtime_support.py tests\test_runtime_support.py.
[2026-04-08 10:20:00 +07:00] Installed pytest into the active user Python 3 environment to enable local regression runs in this workspace. Verified the new runtime traceback logging coverage with `py -3 -m pytest -q tests\test_runtime_support.py` and rechecked callback duplicate handling with `py -3 -m pytest -q tests\test_bot_runtime_manager.py -k duplicate_callback`; both passed. Pytest emitted a non-fatal cache warning because it could not write `.pytest_cache` in this environment.
[2026-04-08 10:27:00 +07:00] Used the new TRACE logging to isolate the recurring `Testing 2` WinError 11 to stale polling-lock PID cleanup, not PayWay. Windows `os.kill(pid, 0)` can raise WinError 11 as well as WinError 87 while probing a dead/invalid PID from the lock file, so _process_exists now treats both as stale/non-running and lets the runtime remove the orphaned lock and continue. Added focused regression coverage for the WinError 11 probe path. Planned verification: py -3 -m pytest -q tests\test_polling_token_lock.py and py -3 -m py_compile src\etrax\standalone\bot_runtime_manager.py tests\test_polling_token_lock.py.
[2026-04-08 10:31:00 +07:00] Verified the stale polling-lock WinError 11 fix with `py -3 -m py_compile src\etrax\standalone\bot_runtime_manager.py tests\test_polling_token_lock.py` and `py -3 -m pytest -q tests\test_polling_token_lock.py -k winerror_11`. The file-wide polling-lock test run is still affected by local pytest temp-directory permission errors on this machine, but the new targeted regression passed.
[2026-04-08 10:38:00 +07:00] Confirmed the `local Telegram polling lock already held` message the user pasted was from before the stale-lock probe fix landed. Inspected `data\polling_locks`, verified the saved lock PIDs were no longer running locally, and cleared the orphaned lock files so `Testing 2` can reacquire polling cleanly on the next start.
[2026-04-08 10:47:00 +07:00] Investigated the report that temporary commands stop working after a bot restart and `/restart` fails to restore the original command menu. Found that handle_message_update was not passing temporary_command_menu_state_store into execute_pipeline, so message-driven callback/command loaders could activate temporary menus only in memory without persisting `temporary_command_menus.json`. Fixed the thread-through, added regression coverage to verify callback-loaded temp menus persist restart state, and added a lazy-recovery `/restart` test to confirm the original command menu is restored after a process restart.
[2026-04-08 10:58:00 +07:00] Smoke-tested the patched temp-menu persistence path against the real `data\bot_processes\testing_2.json` config using BotRuntimeManager runtime snapshot loading plus a direct `/etrex` message dispatch. Verified the current code now activates `tracking location`, republishes the chat-scoped temp commands, and writes the expected entry to a temporary `temporary_command_menus.json` state file. Observed that the user's live `data\temporary_command_menus.json` was still `{}` with an older timestamp, which indicates the currently running runtime process likely had not reloaded the patched code yet.
[2026-04-08 11:05:00 +07:00] Rechecked the current `Testing 2` polling-lock state after the user hit the `local Telegram polling lock already held` error again. Found `data\polling_locks\640b1d46ecc3a9d02865a689934cfc6db87703ce737fd3802019fd2d2ecdf17d.lock` pointing at dead PID `20144`, removed the stale lock, and confirmed the polling-lock directory was empty afterward.
[2026-04-08 11:12:00 +07:00] Investigated why stopping then immediately starting `Testing 2` could still hit the local polling-lock guard. Found a lifecycle race in BotRuntimeManager: stop() only waited 2 seconds, then marked the bot inactive even if the long-poll thread was still alive and still holding the token lock. Updated start/stop lifecycle checks to treat an alive worker thread as still running or stopping until it actually exits, and made stop() wait for roughly the configured poll timeout before returning `stopping` instead of falsely reporting `stopped`. Added focused lifecycle coverage for stop/start while the previous polling thread is still alive.
[2026-04-08 11:24:00 +07:00] Added standalone UI prototype routes for the requested list/form screens in token_ui.py instead of introducing a separate frontend app. Exposed `/ui/working-hours`, `/ui/locations`, and a lightweight `/ui/general-details` placeholder route with a shared tabbed shell, added home-page quick links to those prototype routes, and recreated the screenshot structure for the Working Hours list and Create Location form inside the current eTrax standalone HTTP UI.
[2026-04-08 11:31:00 +07:00] Added direct navigation buttons for the new standalone list/form routes in the existing UI entry points. The main token page header now links straight to `Working Hours` and `Locations`, and the per-bot independent config page now exposes the same direct links alongside the runtime controls so those pages can be opened without going through the prototype-links panel.
[2026-04-08 11:46:00 +07:00] Applied local functionality to the standalone Working Hours and Locations pages in token_ui.py. Wired both routes to dedicated JSON-backed state files (`working_hours_ui.json` and `locations_ui.json`), added POST handlers for create/update/delete actions, hydrated the page renders from saved entries, and made the location form load existing records back into the editor for direct updates. Added focused token_ui coverage for saved-record rendering plus the new form action endpoints, and normalized a location-page badge encoding artifact in the rendered HTML. Planned verification: py -3 -m py_compile src\etrax\standalone\token_ui.py tests\test_token_ui.py and py -3 -m pytest -q tests\test_token_ui.py -k standalone_ui.
[2026-04-08 12:03:00 +07:00] Upgraded the standalone Locations page from a static iframe preview to an interactive map picker. Added a new `/ui/location-search` JSON endpoint in token_ui.py, wired the page to a Leaflet/OpenStreetMap click-and-drag pin, and added server-side location resolution that accepts direct coordinates, standard Google Maps URLs, and short `maps.app.goo.gl` links by following redirects before extracting coordinates. Free-text place search now falls back to Nominatim, and focused token_ui coverage was added for Google Maps coordinate parsing plus direct-coordinate short-circuit search resolution. Planned verification: py -3 -m py_compile src\etrax\standalone\token_ui.py tests\test_token_ui.py and py -3 -m pytest -q tests\test_token_ui.py -k "standalone_ui or location_coordinates or direct_coordinates".
[2026-04-08 12:11:00 +07:00] Extended short Google Maps link handling for the standalone Locations page after a real `maps.app.goo.gl` failure report. The location-search resolver now inspects both the final redirected URL and the returned HTML body, extracting coordinates from Google Maps preview-place payloads when the short link only expands to a partial maps URL without `/@lat,lng` in the address line. Added focused regression coverage for preview-place HTML coordinate extraction and reverified the standalone UI location-search tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 12:16:00 +07:00] Added browser geolocation support to the standalone Locations page. The map search toolbar now exposes a `Use My Location` action that requests `navigator.geolocation`, moves the pin to the device’s current coordinates when permission is granted, and shows clear feedback for denied, unavailable, or timed-out location requests. Reverified the standalone UI location tests with py_compile and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 12:21:00 +07:00] Added a random offset generator to the standalone Locations page. The map toolbar now includes `Random +30 km`, which computes a random bearing from the current pin and moves the marker to a new point about 30 kilometers away while updating the latitude/longitude inputs and map feedback. Extended the standalone UI render coverage for the new button and reverified the focused location-page tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 12:24:00 +07:00] Adjusted the standalone Locations random-pin generator to stay within the requested radius instead of always using the full distance. Renamed the action to `Random Under 30 km`, changed the generated offset distance to a random value between 0 and 30 km from the current pin, updated the user feedback text, and reverified the focused token_ui location tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 12:29:00 +07:00] Repurposed the standalone Locations random generator into a test-entry creator. The toolbar action is now `Generate Test Under 30 km`; it clears the current entry id, generates a fresh test location name/code from the current timestamp, moves the pin to a random point within 30 km of the current pin, and immediately submits the form so the generated record is saved into the locations list as a new entry. Added render coverage for the new label plus the data hooks used by the auto-save action, and reverified the focused token_ui location tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 12:35:00 +07:00] Added a `Load All To Map` action to the standalone Locations page. The page now serializes saved location records into the Leaflet script, and the new button loads every saved location as map markers with popups for name/code/zone/company, keeps the current editable pin visible, and fits the map view to all loaded points. Extended the standalone UI render coverage for the new control and reverified the focused token_ui location tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 12:40:00 +07:00] Enforced the requested 7-row cap on the standalone Working Hours page. The save handler now rejects creation of an eighth row, and the page switches from the add-row form to a `Maximum Reached` state once seven rows are present, with the toolbar showing `7 / 7 Rows` instead of the add shortcut. Added focused render coverage for the capped state and reverified the standalone token_ui tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 12:46:00 +07:00] Cleaned up the standalone Working Hours logic in token_ui.py. Refactored the page to use dedicated normalization/render helpers instead of inline list/string assembly, made saved rows sort automatically by weekday, and added duplicate-day detection so the weekly schedule stays coherent with at most one row per day. Added focused coverage for weekday sorting and duplicate-day conflict detection, then reverified the related token_ui tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 12:50:00 +07:00] Improved the standalone Working Hours add-row UX so the day auto-advances to the next unused weekday. The add form now defaults to the first available day in weekly order instead of always resetting to Monday, which keeps row creation aligned with the one-row-per-day schedule. Added focused coverage for the next-available-day helper and the rendered default selection, then reverified the working-hours token_ui tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 12:54:00 +07:00] Removed the redundant second add action from the standalone Working Hours page. The toolbar no longer shows a separate `+ Add New` shortcut while the inline add form is visible; it now shows the current row count (`n / 7 Rows`) so there is only one add action left on the page. Reverified the focused token_ui working-hours/location tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 12:59:00 +07:00] Restricted the standalone Working Hours day dropdowns to valid remaining weekdays only. The add-row form now lists only unused days, while each existing row keeps its current day plus any other still-available days, which prevents users from selecting already-occupied weekdays through the UI before save-time validation runs. Added focused coverage for the remaining-day option helpers and the add-form rendering, then reverified the relevant token_ui tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 13:03:00 +07:00] Refined the standalone Working Hours day selector behavior so the UI exposes only valid choices per row. Existing rows now render their day dropdown with the current day plus any remaining unused weekdays, and the add-row form renders only unused weekdays with the next available day preselected. Reverified the focused token_ui working-hours/location tests with py_compile plus targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 15:10:00 +07:00] Added closest-saved-location validation to the standalone share_location module. The config/editor/runtime stack now supports enabling a nearest saved-location check against data/locations_ui.json with a configurable meter tolerance plus a retry message template. When enabled, incoming shared locations expose closest-location context fields (name/code/distance/tolerance) to success or invalid templates and continuation modules; locations outside tolerance are rejected and keep the request pending instead of continuing. Updated token_ui/config_vue/Vue module round-trips, extended the runtime resolver and location handler, and added focused coverage in test_share_location_module.py, test_bot_runtime_manager.py, and test_token_ui.py. Reverified with py_compile, node --check, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 15:28:00 +07:00] Added a second share_location saved-location option for lookup-only behavior. The module now supports ind_closest_saved_location separately from match_closest_saved_location, so flows can populate nearest saved-location context from data/locations_ui.json without enforcing the tolerance gate. When the stricter match option is enabled it still rejects out-of-range shares; when only the find option is enabled it accepts the share and exposes the nearest location fields for templates and continuation logic. Updated the standalone Vue editor/config serialization/runtime wiring plus focused tests, then reverified with py_compile, node --check, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 15:45:00 +07:00] Tightened the standalone share_location live-location mode editor so the extra live options are only exposed when require_live_location is enabled and are mutually exclusive via radio inputs instead of independent checkboxes. Added normalization on both the Vue editor side and the token_ui builder/serializer so only one mode survives per step (Track As Breadcrumb over Match Closest Saved Location over Find Closest Saved Location), and hidden stale values are dropped when live location is turned off. Updated focused token_ui share_location tests to cover the gated save behavior and reverified with node --check, py_compile, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-08 16:00:00 +07:00] Refined the standalone share_location live-location mode selector so it reads like a compact mode picker instead of a raw list of radio labels. Replaced the plain stacked options with a two-column card-style radio group that gives each mode a title plus a short behavioral description, added selected-state styling in the shared config-page CSS, and kept the layout responsive down to one column on narrow screens. Added a focused render assertion for the new mode-picker CSS hooks and reverified with node --check, py_compile, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 09:10:00 +07:00] Removed the standalone share_location \Store Location/Breadcrumb By Day\ option from the editor and save path. The visible checkbox and its helper text are gone from the Vue module UI, the hidden form fields were removed from config_vue.js, and the token_ui share_location builder/serializer now stop writing the flag back when a config is edited. Runtime compatibility remains in place for older saved configs, but the setting no longer appears or persists through the standalone editor. Reverified with node --check, py_compile, and targeted share_location pytest coverage.
[2026-04-09 09:20:00 +07:00] Changed the default out-of-range reply for standalone share_location closest-match validation to a simpler message: You are at the wrong location. Updated the core default invalid text, removed the distance-heavy fallback text from the runtime helper, aligned the standalone Vue editor default/placeholder with the new wording, and added focused runtime coverage for the blank-template fallback path. Reverified with node --check, py_compile, and targeted bot_runtime_manager pytest coverage.
[2026-04-09 09:52:00 +07:00] Cleared another stale standalone polling lock for Testing 2. The active token lock file data/polling_locks/640b1d46ecc3a9d02865a689934cfc6db87703ce737fd3802019fd2d2ecdf17d.lock still pointed at dead PID 27556 from 2026-04-08, so it was moved into data/polling_locks/stale/ to unblock startup while preserving the artifact for inspection. Confirmed the active polling_locks directory no longer contains a live token lock file.
[2026-04-09 10:00:00 +07:00] Fixed standalone share_location closest-location validation against the actual Locations page file format. The runtime loader in share_location_module.py previously only accepted a top-level JSON list, but data/locations_ui.json is stored as an object with an entries array, which caused false No saved locations are configured for validation yet. messages even when locations existed. Updated the loader to accept both raw-list and wrapped entries payloads, added focused runtime coverage for the wrapped format, and reverified with py_compile plus targeted bot_runtime_manager pytest coverage.
[2026-04-09 10:08:00 +07:00] Stopped standalone share_location closest-match validation from spamming the same out-of-range message on every repeated location update. Added a per-request closest_location_mismatch_notified flag on PendingLocationRequest and changed the runtime handler to send the invalid/wrong-location message only once per pending request; later repeated out-of-range updates are ignored until the request is completed or restarted. Added focused regression coverage to ensure the first mismatch sends a message and a subsequent edited-message mismatch does not. Reverified with py_compile and targeted bot_runtime_manager pytest coverage.
[2026-04-09 10:18:00 +07:00] Made standalone share_location automatically reply with the nearest saved location when Find Closest Saved Location is enabled and no custom success text is set. Added a dedicated default closest-location success template in the core telegram share_location module, updated the runtime success-text fallback to use it when a nearest location was found, changed the standalone builder to default blank find-mode success text to Closest saved location is {closest_location_name}., and stopped the Vue editor from pre-filling the generic success message so the automatic nearest-location reply can take effect. Added focused runtime and token_ui coverage, then reverified with node --check, py_compile, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 10:24:00 +07:00] Updated the live Testing 2 bot config so the /etrex share_location step explicitly replies with the nearest saved location. The step already had ind_closest_saved_location=true, but it also had a custom success_text_template (Thanks, your location was received good.), which overrode the new automatic closest-location reply. Replaced that custom success text in data/bot_processes/testing_2.json with Closest saved location is {closest_location_name}. and validated the JSON payload.
[2026-04-09 10:30:00 +07:00] Added optional Telegram Group ID support to the standalone Locations page. The field now appears in the create/edit form, persists into data/locations_ui.json, reloads when editing an existing location, appears in the saved location cards, and is included in the map popup data payload. Updated the location-page render coverage to include the new field and reverified with py_compile plus targeted token_ui pytest coverage.
[2026-04-09 11:32:00 +07:00] Added standalone share_location group-notification support for Find Closest Saved Location when the matched saved location has a Telegram Group ID. Wired the new closest_location_group_text_template field through the standalone config save/load path in token_ui.py, preserved it in command/callback row extraction and temporary-command parsing, and updated the runtime resolver/closest-location context loader so locations_ui.json telegram_group_id values are exposed as closest_location_telegram_group_id. The share_location runtime now sends a second rendered message to that group chat when find_closest_saved_location is active, the group template is configured, and the closest saved location includes a Telegram Group ID. Added focused token_ui and bot_runtime_manager regression coverage, then reverified with py_compile and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 11:36:00 +07:00] Updated the live Testing 2 /etrex share_location step to include a closest_location_group_text_template so Find Closest Saved Location can send a notification to the matched location's Telegram Group ID. The runtime and editor support were already in place, but the active bot config only had find_closest_saved_location plus the user-chat success template, so no group message could be emitted until the step carried a group message template as well. Validated the edited JSON payload with py -3 -m json.tool.
[2026-04-09 11:40:00 +07:00] Hardened standalone share_location closest-location group notifications so Telegram delivery failures no longer abort the main user flow. When Find Closest Saved Location tries to send the optional closest_location_group_text_template to a saved location's Telegram Group ID and Telegram rejects the target chat (for example Bad Request: chat not found), the runtime now logs the group-notification failure and continues returning the normal user-chat success message instead of crashing the entire update. Added focused bot_runtime_manager coverage for both successful group delivery and rejected-group fallback, then reverified with py_compile and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 11:48:00 +07:00] Moved standalone share_location Find Closest Saved Location group notifications to the end of the location flow so they can use context gathered by continuation modules that run after the initial location share. The user-chat success reply still sends immediately, but the optional closest_location_group_text_template now waits until execute_pipeline finishes mutating context, then renders and sends to the matched saved location's Telegram Group ID. Retained the earlier non-fatal fallback for rejected group chats and added focused runtime coverage proving the delayed group message can use a continuation-updated field plus the rejected-group fallback path. Reverified with py_compile and targeted bot_runtime_manager pytest coverage.
[2026-04-09 12:02:00 +07:00] Added configurable timing for standalone share_location closest-location group notifications. Find Closest Saved Location now supports closest_location_group_send_timing with Right Away, At End, and After Step #N behavior plus an optional closest_location_group_send_after_step value. Wired the new fields through the standalone Vue editor, hidden config form inputs, token_ui save/load and row extraction helpers, JSON chain serialization/parsing, and the runtime resolver. The share_location runtime now sends the optional group message immediately, after a requested continuation step number, or after all continuation modules finish, while still treating rejected group sends or invalid group-message templates as non-fatal. Added focused runtime coverage for end timing, after-step timing, and failure fallback, plus token_ui coverage for the new config roundtrip. Reverified with node --check, py_compile, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 13:05:00 +07:00] Added a new standalone ask_selfie Telegram flow module that prompts the current user to send a selfie photo, waits for an incoming photo message, stores the largest Telegram photo file metadata in context, replies with configurable success/invalid templates, and then continues the remaining pipeline modules. Wired the new AskSelfieConfig/PendingSelfieRequest runtime path through the standalone runtime registry, bot runtime manager request stores, forget_user_data cleanup, token_ui save/load and chain-step serialization helpers, plus a new standalone Vue editor module script so the step can be configured from the existing builder UI. Added focused coverage in test_ask_selfie_module.py, test_bot_runtime_manager.py, and test_token_ui.py, then reverified with py_compile, node --check, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 13:28:00 +07:00] Added a standalone custom_code Telegram flow module that lets the builder select one public method from src/etrax/standalone/custom_code_functions.py and execute it at runtime. Created CustomCodeConfig/CustomCodeModule in the core Telegram layer, a standalone function-provider class with example methods, a runtime module spec/builder, and a dedicated Vue editor module that renders a function dropdown populated from the editable StandaloneCustomCodeFunctions class. Wired the new function_name field through token_ui config state, config_vue hidden inputs and editor seed normalization, module_system step normalization, command/callback/start save-load extraction, temporary-command JSON roundtrip, and chain-step serialization/parsing so custom_code works as a primary step or chained continuation step. Added focused regression coverage in test_custom_code_module.py, test_bot_runtime_manager.py, and test_token_ui.py, then reverified with py_compile, node --check, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 13:42:00 +07:00] Added short template aliases for standalone share_location delayed closest-location group notifications so the group message can use shorter placeholders after later modules gather more data. The group-message renderer in share_location_module.py now builds an alias-enriched render context before formatting closest_location_group_text_template, including shortcuts for closest saved location fields (closest_name, closest_code, closest_distance, closest_distance_m, closest_company, closest_zone, closest_group_id, closest_lat, closest_lng), shared-contact fields (phone, contact_first, contact_last, contact_name, contact_id), live/shared location fields (lat, lng, accuracy, live_period, heading, alert_radius), and selfie fields (selfie, selfie_id, selfie_unique, selfie_caption, selfie_count). Added focused bot_runtime_manager coverage proving delayed group messages can render those short aliases after continuation modules populate the underlying long-form context keys, then reverified with py_compile and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 13:49:00 +07:00] Added a quick-insert shortcut toolbar to the standalone share_location editor for Closest Location Group Message templates. The Find Closest Saved Location config UI in share_location_module.js now renders clickable token buttons above the group-message textarea so operators can insert common delayed-template aliases like {closest_name}, {closest_code}, {phone}, {contact_name}, {selfie}, {lat}, and {lng} without typing them manually. Reverified the updated standalone Vue module script with node --check.
[2026-04-09 13:55:00 +07:00] Updated standalone share_location closest-location group-message shortcuts so {location} now renders a Google Maps link built from the shared location latitude/longitude, replacing the old quick-insert reliance on separate {lat} and {lng} placeholders. The group-message alias builder in share_location_module.py now emits location=https://www.google.com/maps?q=<lat>,<lng> whenever the shared location coordinates are present, the quick-insert toolbar in share_location_module.js now offers {location} instead of separate lat/lng tokens, and focused bot_runtime_manager coverage now asserts the generated group message contains the Google Maps URL. Reverified with node --check, py_compile, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 14:22:00 +07:00] Extended standalone share_location closest-location group notifications into a configurable group action runner so Find Closest Saved Location can now either send one templated group message, execute a callback module pipeline in the matched location group chat, or run a standalone custom-code function against that group chat. Added closest_location_group_action_type plus callback/custom-code target fields to ShareLocationConfig/PendingLocationRequest, threaded them through the standalone Vue editor, hidden config form fields, token_ui save-load helpers, raw module extraction, and JSON serialization, and updated runtime_update_router so location-reply handlers receive command_modules for nested callback execution. The share_location runtime now builds a group-scoped context, preserves origin chat/user metadata, supports callback-module group actions via execute_pipeline, supports custom-code group actions via resolve_custom_code_function with a fixed token resolver, and retains the existing delayed timing controls (right away, end, after step #). Added focused token_ui and bot_runtime_manager coverage for callback and custom-code group actions, then reverified with node --check, py_compile, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 14:33:00 +07:00] Extended the standalone send_photo module so its photo field can render context templates instead of only static URLs or file IDs. SendTelegramPhotoModule now resolves configured photo values like {selfie_file_id} against runtime context before calling Telegram, which allows a later send_photo step to resend the image captured by ask_selfie without extra custom code. Updated the standalone send_photo editor copy to advertise URL, file ID, or template usage and added quick-insert buttons for {selfie_file_id} and {photo}. Added focused unit coverage in tests/test_send_photo_module.py for successful selfie-file rendering and missing-template-field validation, then reverified with node --check, py_compile, and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-09 14:39:00 +07:00] Checked the live Testing 2 standalone bot config after the user reported that Closest Location Group Action was not running callback group_notify. The runtime code path was already capable of callback-module execution, but data/bot_processes/testing_2.json still had the share_location step saved as closest_location_group_action_type="message" with closest_location_group_text_template, so the runtime never attempted the callback lookup. Updated the live etrex share_location step to closest_location_group_action_type="callback_module" with closest_location_group_callback_key="group_notify" and revalidated the JSON structure with json.tool.
[2026-04-09 16:08:00 +07:00] Fixed delayed closest-location group callback execution so end/after-step actions attach into stored continuations for awaiting modules like ask_selfie, preventing group callbacks from firing before selfie_file_id exists. Updated focused bot runtime tests for deferred step-count semantics; py_compile and pytest tests\test_bot_runtime_manager.py -k "group_callback_until_after_selfie_completion or group_callback_pipeline or group_message or find_closest" passed.
[2026-04-09 16:34:00 +07:00] Added standalone send_location module support so workflows and group callbacks can send a real Telegram map pin from shared coordinates. Implemented Bot API sendLocation transport, core send_location module, runtime wrapper, standalone Vue editor, config hidden fields, token_ui parser/builders/chain roundtrip support, and focused tests for send_location plus token_ui roundtrip. Verified with py_compile, node --check, pytest tests\test_send_location_module.py, pytest tests\test_token_ui.py -k "send_location or share_location or custom_code", and pytest tests\test_bot_runtime_manager.py -k "group_callback_until_after_selfie_completion or group_callback_pipeline or group_message or find_closest".
[2026-04-09 16:39:00 +07:00] Changed send_location behavior to send a Google Maps URL message instead of Telegram native sendLocation, using https://www.google.com/maps?q={lat},{lng}. Updated the send_location module result payload, editor hint text, and focused send_location tests; py_compile, node --check, and pytest tests\test_send_location_module.py tests\test_token_ui.py -k "send_location" passed.
[2026-04-09 16:48:00 +07:00] Added a derived {location} shortcut to standalone send_message templates so messages can render one Google Maps URL from shared location coordinates without requiring separate {location_latitude}/{location_longitude} placeholders. SendTelegramMessageModule now enriches its render context with location=https://www.google.com/maps?q=<lat>,<lng> whenever location_latitude and location_longitude are present, the standalone send_message editor toolbar now includes a quick-insert Location token button, and focused unit coverage in tests/test_send_message_module.py now verifies the rendered URL text. Reverified with py_compile, node --check, and targeted pytest for send_message.
[2026-04-10 09:12:00 +07:00] Fixed chained share_location config reload so Closest Location Group Action type, callback key, and custom-code function survive page save/reload. The standalone editor already serialized these fields into JSON chain_steps for non-primary modules, but token_ui.py only reloaded the group message text and timing when parsing serialized share_location chain steps, so chained steps silently fell back to the default message action on the next load. Updated the JSON chain-step parser to pass closest_location_group_action_type, closest_location_group_callback_key, and closest_location_group_custom_code_function_name back into _parse_share_location_chain_step, and added focused token_ui coverage proving a callback_module group action with group_notify round-trips correctly through _parse_chain_steps. Reverified with py_compile, node --check config_vue.js, and targeted pytest tests/test_token_ui.py -k "share_location_group or parse_chain_steps_preserves_share_location_group_callback_action".
[2026-04-10 09:26:00 +07:00] Relaxed standalone share_location group-action persistence so the selected Closest Location Group Action mode survives save/reload even before its target details are filled. Previously token_ui.py only wrote closest_location_group_action_type for callback/custom-code modes when a callback key or custom-code function name was already present, which made the UI snap back to the default Send Message mode if the operator selected Run Callback Module first and planned to fill the callback key later. Updated _build_share_location_step and _pipeline_to_chain_steps to always persist the normalized group action type for find_closest_saved_location steps, keep timing metadata for non-message modes, and only treat message mode as active when a non-empty group message template exists. Mirrored the same behavior in share_location_module.js formatChain for consistency and added focused token_ui coverage proving callback_module mode stays saved even with an empty callback key. Reverified with py_compile, node --check share_location_module.js, and targeted pytest tests/test_token_ui.py -k "share_location_group or parse_chain_steps_preserves_share_location_group_callback_action or preserves_share_location_group_action_type_without_callback_key".
[2026-04-10 09:41:00 +07:00] Added hard cache-busting for standalone config-page JavaScript assets and strengthened the share_location group-action selector event binding to reduce stale-editor behavior during local UI work. The config page now appends a version query derived from the latest mtime across token_ui.py, config_vue.js, the vendored Vue runtime, and all standalone vue_modules so browser reloads fetch the updated editor scripts after local code changes. Also updated the Closest Location Group Action Type <select> in share_location_module.js to write on both change and input events. Reverified with py_compile, node --check share_location_module.js, and targeted pytest tests/test_token_ui.py -k "share_location_group or parse_chain_steps_preserves_share_location_group_callback_action or preserves_share_location_group_action_type_without_callback_key".
[2026-04-10 09:51:00 +07:00] Rebuilt the standalone share_location Closest Location Group Action Type control from a plain <select> into the same radio-card mode picker style used elsewhere in the location editor. The new UI writes the action type explicitly on radio change for Send Message, Run Callback Module, and Run Custom Code, which removes one more fragile path where the old message value could remain selected in the chain-step editor. Reverified with node --check share_location_module.js and targeted token_ui pytest coverage for share_location group-action roundtrips.
[2026-04-10 10:03:00 +07:00] Hardened standalone share_location group-action saving so the backend and frontend both infer the real action type from the configured group-action fields, not only from the explicit Action Type selector. Added _resolve_closest_location_group_action_type in token_ui.py and the mirrored resolveClosestLocationGroupActionType helper in share_location_module.js so a non-empty closest_location_group_callback_key forces callback_module mode, a non-empty closest_location_group_custom_code_function_name forces custom_code mode, and only a text template alone keeps message mode. This protects saving when the Action Type control is stale but the operator has already filled a callback key like group_notify. Added focused token_ui coverage proving a stale message-mode input plus callback key still saves as callback_module. Reverified with py_compile, node --check share_location_module.js, and targeted pytest tests/test_token_ui.py -k "share_location_group or parse_chain_steps_preserves_share_location_group_callback_action or preserves_share_location_group_action_type_without_callback_key or prefers_callback_group_action_when_callback_key_present".
[2026-04-10 10:11:00 +07:00] Updated the share_location Closest Location Group Action radio picker to clear incompatible stale fields when switching modes. Selecting Run Callback Module now clears the old group message text and custom-code function; selecting Run Custom Code clears the old group message text and callback key; selecting Send Message clears the callback key and custom-code function. This avoids mixed saved state where an old closest_location_group_text_template kept forcing message mode even after the operator switched the action type in the UI. Reverified with node --check share_location_module.js and targeted share_location token_ui pytest coverage.
[2026-04-10 10:26:00 +07:00] Added standalone token_ui config-save debug logging so each save now prints both the raw submitted form payload and the final JSON payload written to disk. This is aimed at the unresolved Closest Location Group Action persistence issue, making it possible to see whether the browser is posting the expected action fields and whether token_ui.py mutates them before writing data/bot_processes/*.json. Reverified with py_compile for src/etrax/standalone/token_ui.py.
[2026-04-10 11:18:00 +07:00] Added debounced autosave to the standalone config editor and fixed another share_location group-action persistence gap. The config page form now posts background autosaves to /config/save with an AJAX header and shows a small autosave status line while preserving the manual Save Config button. token_ui.py now returns JSON for autosave requests instead of redirecting, while normal saves still redirect. In the Vue editor stack, module_system.js now preserves closest_location_group_action_type plus the callback/custom-code target fields during normalization so chain-step JSON no longer drops them, and share_location_module.js no longer emits broken radio field names like closest-location-group-action-[object Object]. Reverified with py_compile for token_ui.py and node --check for config_vue.js, module_system.js, and share_location_module.js.
[2026-04-10 11:27:00 +07:00] Removed the temporary standalone config-save debug payload printing from token_ui.py after using it to trace the Closest Location Group Action save issue. The config editor keeps the new autosave flow and JSON autosave endpoint behavior, but terminal output no longer dumps the raw form payload or the final saved payload on every save. Reverified with py_compile for src/etrax/standalone/token_ui.py.
[2026-04-10 11:34:00 +07:00] Switched the standalone send_location module back to Telegram native map pins instead of plain Google Maps URLs. SendTelegramLocationModule in core/telegram/send_location.py now calls gateway.send_location with resolved latitude/longitude, the standalone send_location editor hint now states that it sends a native Telegram map pin, and the focused send_location unit test now verifies the native location payload/result structure. Reverified with py_compile for send_location.py and pytest for tests/test_send_location_module.py.
[2026-04-10 11:49:00 +07:00] Fixed nested callback pipelines stopping after the first immediate module. Added a continue_immediately signal to SendTelegramPhotoModule and SendTelegramLocationModule, then updated runtime_update_router.execute_pipeline to run nested continuation_modules after a successful non-skipped outcome only for modules that explicitly opt into immediate continuation. This preserves deferred behavior for interaction-driven modules like inline_button, share_contact, ask_selfie, and share_location while allowing group callback pipelines such as send_photo -> send_message to execute fully. Added focused bot runtime coverage for a closest-location group callback pipeline whose SendTelegramPhotoModule continuation sends a second group message, then reverified with py_compile and targeted pytest.
[2026-04-10 12:02:00 +07:00] Updated the standalone send_location editor defaults so new send_location steps start with the shared location context keys already populated. The Vue module default step in send_location_module.js now pre-fills location_latitude with {location_latitude} and location_longitude with {location_longitude}, which makes a newly added send_location module immediately target the user-shared coordinates without requiring manual button clicks. Reverified with node --check for src/etrax/standalone/vue_modules/send_location_module.js.
[2026-04-10 12:07:00 +07:00] Simplified the standalone send_location editor from two separate latitude/longitude inputs into one combined Location Template input. The Vue editor still stores location_latitude and location_longitude under the hood for runtime compatibility, but the UI now shows a single field that reads and writes `lat, lng` plus quick buttons for Shared Location and Closest Location. Reverified with node --check for src/etrax/standalone/vue_modules/send_location_module.js.
[2026-04-10 12:56:00 +07:00] Added a reusable standalone bind_code workflow module so commands or callbacks can generate and bind incremental user codes like ETX-0001 on each run. Implemented a new core BindCodeConfig/BindCodeModule plus a file-backed JsonBoundCodeStore persisted in data/bound_codes.json, wired the store through the standalone runtime manager/factory/registry, added a new bind_code Vue editor with prefix/number-width/start-number fields, and threaded those fields through config_vue.js autosave hidden inputs plus token_ui.py save/load, row extraction, temporary-command serialization, and JSON chain-step parsing/serialization. Added focused coverage in tests/test_bind_code_module.py and tests/test_token_ui.py, then reverified with py_compile for touched Python files, node --check for the new/updated editor scripts, pytest tests/test_bind_code_module.py, pytest tests/test_token_ui.py -k "bind_code or share_location_group or parse_chain_steps", and a direct runtime registry/factory smoke import for bind_code resolution/building.
